<br>
How much money does your school get? Probably not enough to install several metal detectors. If your school is in a building (as opposed to an open campus), then everyone will be hanging around outside before school starts. Once school starts, and people start filing through the doors, they'll have to go through the metal detectors. Unless you have several of them set up, it'll be a bitch to get everyone through quickly and efficiently. Then you have to account for watches, calculators, jewelry, etc, which might get stolen or dropped or misplaced, causing even more of a delay. <br>
<br>
Then you'll have to hire people to stand watch at the metal detectors for several hours a day. After all, not all students come to school at the same time, some don't have classes during some periods, some come late, etc. Sure, you can have someone stand there only during certain types of the day, for example only the start of the period, but that would kind of make the detectors pointless. After all, if someone wants to sneak a gun through, they can just wait until no one is on watch.<br>
<br>
Example: Metal detectors at airports. Huge delays there.<br>
<br>
Personally I think metal detectors are a terrible idea. Inefficient, and there are always ways around it if anyone truly wanted to shoot up the school.<br>
<br>
Conclusion: Unless your school can afford enough metal detectors (and guards) to get everyone through in a quick and efficient way, it's going to result in a lot of tardies to first period class. <p><img src=http://nasbin.homestead.com/files/hamburglar.jpg><BR><font size=1>Nasbin Wasbinbobasbin
